window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Stampeding Bingbuffers. Angry locals. No good deed goes unpunished....</p> <p>After hearing reports of Wampus attacks at a pipeline in rural Missouri, Mason and Emma head out to investigate. They quickly learn the Wampus is as friendly as they come. However, something far deadlier is stalking the forest.</p> <p>The woods come to life around them as they run for their lives, swarming with more creatures than they could have imagined. Now, self-preservation will mean balancing their desire to protect the endangered cryptids and fighting to survive.</p> <p>Can they stop what's behind the mysterious pipeline deaths? Or will their own blood be spilled like an oil slick?</p> <p><i>Mason Dixon - The Wampus of Reeds Spring</i> is the second book in Eric R. Asher's side-splitting New Templars Novella urban fantasy series. Looking for a witty listen full of bizarre creatures? Join Masonâ€™s fast-paced adventures today!</p>"; 
